This paper deals with data-driven modelling of interconnected systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the concept of network identifiability, which is related to machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG), as well as the use of path-based topological properties to derive conditions for single module identifiability, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
